communion'''Communion''' may refer to:Religion*Communion (sacrament) or Eucharist or the Lord's Supper, the Christian rite involving the eating of bread and drinking of wine, reenacting the Last Supper** Communion rite, that part of the Eucharistic rite in which the consecrated bread and wine are distributed to participants in the Catholic mass** Communion (chant), the Gregorian chant that accompanies this rite*Communion (Christian), the relationship between Christians as individuals or churches* Communion of Saints, a doctrine of Christianity mentioned in the Apostles' CreedEntertainment* ''Communion'' (book), a book by Whitley Strieber about his purported abductions by aliens** Communion (1989 film), a film based on the book* ''Alice, Sweet Alice'' or ''Communion'', a 1976 horror film starring Brooke ShieldsMusic* Communion (music), an artist-led music community* ''Communion'' (Roy Campbell album) (1995)* ''Communion'' (John Patitucci album) (2001)* ''Communion'' (Septic Flesh album) (2008)* ''Communion'' (The Soundtrack of Our Lives album) (2008)* Communion (Years ; Years album)|''Communion'' (Years ; Years album) (2015)* "Communion",  a song by Debbie Harry from ''Debravation''* "Communion", a song by Third Day from ''Wherever You Are''See also* ''Communio'', a theological journal